cs.PL, cs.AR, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.LO. 

The paper presents a new language for dataflow programming, which is a subfield of programming languages (cs.PL). The language design focuses on addressing the problem of potentially infinite computation in cyclic dataflow networks, which is a topic in computer architecture (cs.AR) and systems engineering (cs.SE). The language also has a synchronous mode of propagation, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY) and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
